authLoginLostPhrasePopupContent:
Anytype cannot recover your Recovery Phrase for you

Currently, there are no methods of accessing your recovery phrase, as we do not store a copy of it. Check out the other places where it might stored:

  • In system password storage. We did it for you automatically
  • Inside a password manager if you use one
  • On a piece of paper stored in a secure place chosen prior
authDeleteDescriptionDeleted: All logged-in devices may have your data stored locally. However, you are not able to sign into Anytype on new devices using your Recovery Phrase.
authOnboardMoreInfo: You can find your Recovery Phrase later in Anytype settings
